    Page: 667
Tags:
  - Beauty-Peace=Beauty=The Uncreate Source of Beauty
By: Plotinus
---
Since there is this Good in any good thing. It must enter from elsewhere (than
the world of things); that Source must be a Good absolute and unique. Thus is
revealed to us the Primarily Existent, the Good, above all that has being,
Good unalloyed, all-transcending, Cause of all. The Maker, as the more
consummate, must surpass the made.
